1 olive oil
1 carrot
1 onion
¼ tsp salt
1 tsp brown sugar
1 packet Onion Chutney
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet salmon
1 packet mayonnaise
1 white turnip
1 Kumara
1 sachet Creole spice blend

Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Cut the carrot, white turnip and kumara into bite-sized chunks. Cut the red onion into wedges. Divide the carrot, white turnip, kumara and onion over two lined oven trays. Drizzle generously with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Add a dash of water to the tray, toss to coat, then spread out evenly and roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

While the veggies are roasting, pat the salmon dry with paper towel and season both sides. Combine the Creole spice blend, salt, brown sugar and a drizzle of olive oil in a medium bowl. Season with pepper, then add the salmon, turning gently to coat. Set aside.

In a small bowl, combine the onion chutney with a splash of water. Mix well and set aside.

When the veggies have 10 minutes cook time remaining, return the frying pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When the oil is hot, cook the salmon, skin-side down first, until just cooked through, 2-4 minutes each side. Remove the pan from the heat, then add the onion chutney mixture and turn the salmon to coat.

When the veggies are done, add the baby spinach leaves to the tray and toss to combine. Season to taste.

Divide the roast veggie toss between plates. Top with the Creole salmon. Spoon over the remaining glaze from the pan. Serve with the mayonnaise.